  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Came up in #4798.\r\n\r\n``Type::canLiveOutsideStorage`` seems to mainly be used for mappings - we may want to consider removing it and using a shared flag for storage references and mappings instead. Also in ``TypeChecker::visit(FunctionDefinition const& _function)`` we should allow such types as arguments and return values for internal functions in general (currently mappings are allowed explicitly), but we have to recheck whether this requires new tests, etc.",
