    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Also, we should better unify mappings and reference types (not through inheritance but perhaps through a shared bool function) - we often have special cases that apply to reference types and to mappings.\r\n\r\nThe `canLiveOutsideStorage` could be replaced by a function that tells whether the type has a name or not, because we have many weird types (TypeType, MagicType, ``super``, ...) which should not be exposed.",
